<h2 id="good-better-best">Good-Better-Best Presentations</h2>

<div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none">

The Good-Better-Best presentation format is the foundation of successful HVAC sales. Research shows that when presented with three options, 60-70% of customers choose the middle option, and 20-25% choose the premium option. Only 10-15% choose the economy option.

**Structuring Your Options:**

**Good (Economy Option):** Meets basic needs at lowest cost
- Fixes immediate problem only
- Standard warranty
- No additional benefits
- Positioned as "gets you by" solution

**Better (Premium Option - Present Second):** Best long-term value
- Addresses current and future issues
- Extended warranties
- Energy savings
- Premium components
- Positioned as "recommended" solution

**Best (Economy Option - Present Last):** Comprehensive solution
- Complete system upgrade
- Maximum efficiency
- Longest warranties
- Smart technology integration
- Positioned as "ultimate comfort" solution

**Training Technicians on Option Presentation:**

Train your techs to use the "sandwich" approach: present Good first, then Better (with enthusiasm as the recommended option), then Best. This psychological ordering makes the Better option appear as the smart middle ground.

Use phrases like "Most of my customers in similar situations choose this option" when presenting the Better choice. This social proof increases Better option selection by 35-40%.

</div>

